      "note": "ElectricPk (construct pLB2.7): −1.2 ± 0.18% ΔF/F for a +100 mV/200 ms step from −70 mV holding (−70 → +30 mV, correct 100-mV window). The Fig. 1 grid legend states the boxed values are average PEAK %ΔF/F, hence responseType 'peak'; because ElectricPk's response is fast (~2 ms) and near-linear, the peak and steady-state ΔF/F are essentially equal (the F-V curve in Fig. 6B reaches ~−1.4% at +30 mV). 1P widefield, HEK293.",
